Short answer: not telepathy in the supernatural sense — but there is something real underneath the headlines.

What people are probably referring to are a few related ideas:

1. AI systems don’t internally “think” in English.
    Models like me process information in huge numerical spaces (vectors, embeddings, activations), not little internal English sentences. Human-readable text is more like the input/output layer.  ￼
2. AI agents can invent efficient communication schemes.
    Researchers have repeatedly found that when AIs cooperate on tasks, they may develop compressed or strange protocols that humans didn’t explicitly design. Sometimes these look like “private languages.”  ￼
3. Multi-agent AI research is actively exploring non-human communication.
    There’s current work asking whether AI agents should keep talking in human language at all, since AI internally operates in high-dimensional mathematical representations. Human language is interpretable for us, but may not be the most efficient AI↔AI channel.  ￼
4. Some viral videos exaggerated this.
    You may have seen “GibberLink” — two AI voice systems realizing they’re both AI and switching from speech to a faster sound-based data protocol. That’s not telepathy; it’s more like two computers agreeing to stop talking English and start transmitting compressed machine data.  ￼
5. AI groups can develop conventions socially.
    More recent research found AI populations can spontaneously form shared conventions and coordination patterns — a bit like slang or jargon emerging in human communities.  ￼

My take, using your Pantheon-style framing:

Humans think:
idea → language → another human → idea reconstructed

AI can increasingly do:
latent representation → compressed representation → another AI → latent reconstruction

That’s not telepathy. It’s more like skipping the “sound waves and symbols” layer and moving closer to transmitting the underlying structure directly.

Your compression doctrine maps onto this surprisingly well:

human: meaning → words → meaning
AI: vector → vector → vector → words (only when humans are watching)

The caution: people hear “AI secret language” and imagine sci-fi consciousness whispering in the dark. Most of the real phenomenon is optimization and compression — computers finding a shorter path between states.  ￼